column2: i’m nova richmond! 🌼 momma’s gonna tell you how they came up with my name...
the huz + i started to talk about names. i remembered that the breeder lived off lexington
column3: no lex or lexi tho. that name was familiar
column4: and i remembered it was a street name in the kids’ favorite movie. the main character was named viktor navorski (can you name that movie??)
column5: and i joked about naming her navorski! then i said “how bout nova?”
column6: and he really liked it. when i looked up what it meant (a star that gets brighter + brighter)
column7: it was symbolic of me today. then when i read that in latin it means new
column8: i was sold! a new chapter in my/our lives for sure
column9: after learning i have c-ptsd from narcissistic abuse
column10: and now have to go through a road to recovery...

column2: so naturally people asked what nova’s was. i wasn’t sure if i wanted to give her a middle name
column3: but out of nowhere ‘richmond’ popped in my head. that’s my hometown
column4: i grew up there. since my childhood was damaged
column5: how fitting to be able to have a = new richmond! 🤗

column1: 1) she’ll let you hold her like a baby and stare deep into your eyes like you’re the only person that matters in the world
2) she will charge you and growl at you and bite you like you are one of her brothers!

column2: so obviously we are still training her how to act properly in our household. she’s suuuuuper social!! everyone who comes through our door will get the most excited + happy greeting from our wiggly-butt furball! 😍👅🥰 nova is pretty much crate-trained. she no longer pees in her crate when we’re gone
column3: tho we come home every 3-4hrs to let her out. we’re working on stretching out that time.

column1: c-ptsd + fibro update: she is always by my side. separation anxiety is a real struggle. we’re working with her on this by allowing her to spend more time with each kid + the huz alone
column2: and sleeping with them on some nights. she’s definitely “my” dog
column3: and knows to be there as my comfort. tho
column4: i need her to know that i can take care of myself sometimes! 😜

column1: 18072;instagram;2019-02-19 09:09:36;FALSE;"it’s taken a lot for me to defy the diet industry.
i don’t consider it the key factor in my eating disorder (because eating disorders do not revolve around just self esteem let me tell you that another time)
column2: but it did play a key role in triggering such a dark and life threatening time in my life.

column1: i’ve fought a war for years and years against diet and beauty culture and i’m proud to say that i believe i’m well beyond “diet culture”
column2: but it really breaks my heart to see how it affects those around me. coworkers between 40-60 telling me they need to lose weight because they “don’t like themselves” and i rebuttal with “what/who has made you dislike yourself? because it isn’t natural to dislike yourself”.

column1: friends who are in their 20’s who are critiquing their legs because they’re “too muscly” which to i say who the hell taught you that there is flaw in women with muscle and strength.
having 13 year olds in my personal messages asking me how to have a “flat stomach?” like having a natural protective layer of fat around your uterus and stomach is something to be ashamed of.

column2: i’m mad; heck i’m furious. because i’ve seen how these blatantly obvious and sometimes extremely subliminal messages can destroy self confidence and in turn destroy lives. and so when these beautiful women (and handsome men
column3: because men are not excluded from the harsh messages of masculinity and appearance) approach me with their body concerns
column4: i will continue to challenge their beliefs and help them realise that they have been lied to! that stretch marks and body fat and cellulite and wrinkles and small boobs and big thighs and everything in between is beautiful! focus on health and self love and continue to challenge the messages you are fed and your entire life will change; believe me 🥰 because i have been in the pits of self loathing and have since achieved a level of self love and confidence that has empowered me like never before 💖";;en;;;;;;0;;emilymarni;Too Sassy For My Own Good;;0;False;17;0;0;322;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/ceeb6327be6b22cd7f7a7756e0966753/5D023B31/t51.2885-15/e35/p1080x1080/50851603_425104071566785_8322894073055828558_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;"it’s taken a lot for me to defy the diet industry.

column1: 18078;instagram;2019-02-19 09:21:20;FALSE;"best decision i made was getting off my ass and using my time wisely.....
i use my lunchtime break for training daily and me and my tane do our best to train weekends💕.
the progression i have had from being consistent and not making up bullshit has been awesome 🙌🏽
the goals to have a happy healthy relationship with my body and i’m working on that and the results are just a bonus.
you have the power to turn your mental health struggles into a positive i chose the gym because i love training and clearing my head alone at the gym.
🖤you deserve to be the best version of yourself 🖤

column1: 18087;instagram;2019-02-15 17:18:11;FALSE;"this book is kind of simply plotted yet bit complex to understand still worth loving not your main stream kind of read. the narration
column2: the main lead was not very appealing to me in the beginning still as i dug deep into this book i unfolded stuff i loved very much. i liked the character of atticus finch the most. i don't know what i loved more about him? his character as a lawyer or his character as a father? and oh! god his last speech in the court room as he finished i thought (it's a spoiler i can't tell you but believe me i loved that part the most.) the conclusion of the story was something that usually happens in the world. something that was quite natural. the writer simply didn't try to satisfy the ordinary readers like me. the writer narrated what is truth
column3: what must be called real. this book deserves a read. i love it. it's a sin to kill a mocking bird ;)

i was reminded that being a women is an advantage. it always has been.
i’ve had the unbelievable privilege of having a grandma that never let being a woman make one damn bit of difference in her success.
she was a valedictorian at her high school
she was told many years ago she was “more qualified” than the men for a management position at the bank she worked at. you know what she did
column2: she worked hard and made it impossible for them to avoid hiring her.

column1: she was then put in a position to provide for her family. gramps couldn’t work
column2: so she rose to the occasion. she quickly became incredibly successful and completely self made. i grew up in a world where the grandma was the bread winner and she gave her husband an allowance.

column3: she never used her gender as something that held her back. she rose to the top with joy

column1: she’s never burned her bra or screamed loudly. she gracefully went into a mans world and took it the fuck over.

column3: this is my grandma. i’m in my mid 30’s. this wasn’t recently
column4: this was in the midst of an era where this shit wasn’t normal.

column1: her story is incredible and shows that women can do anything.
so get out there and own it. own being a women
column2: get out there and get it. no excuses.

column1: 18170;instagram;2019-02-19 05:29:50;FALSE;"february 18th. it’s not my favorite day and february has been my least favorite month for the past few years. 3 years ago
column2: i was raped on a first date.

column1: to my rapist - a big fuck you and i hope your trial/conviction was a lesson for you. i hope you never do to anyone else
every year since then has been different - the first year i cried and stayed home all day
column2: last year i cried some and spent the day with ally and hunter eating burgers at one of my happy places
column3: and this year i actually forgot about what day it was until my family’s therapist texted me to ask if i wanted to talk or needed extra support today. when i realized what day it was
column4: i cried for a few minutes while my incredibly supportive and kind boyfriend held me and reminded me that i was safe in that moment.

column1: i’ve actually been more stressed and anxious leading up to today than i have been during the day itself. today
column2: i spent the first half with my boyfriend - by far the most stellar human i’ve ever had the privilege of dating. we coincidentally got breakfast at the same café i sat at two years ago
column3: eating by myself and trying to prepare for the trial against my rapist that i would attend in a couple hours. then i got to spend a few hours with mariah
column5: which always makes my heart happy. we finally went to this cute little matcha café and ate to our heart’s content. and now
column6: i’m home in federal way eating teriyaki with my parents. it’s been a simple day
column7: with a lot of light hearted-ness and little joys. but it’s been a rough month
column8: with some added anxiety and extra hyper vigilance.

column1: my life is pretty busy right now
column2: i work at the ram 4 days
column3: at my internship at ryther 2 days
column4: and coaching 1 day. i have classes that i both enjoy and am ready to be done with. i am graduating in june from my dream school with a degree i am proud of. i have no idea what i’ll be doing after graduation
column5: but right now i am happy. i am supported and cared for. thank you to everyone who’s been a part of my healing the past few years
column6: it really has been an arduous journey. i didn’t think i’d be happy in college
column7: let alone as incredibly content and loved as i am right now.

column6: it really has been an arduous journey. i didn’t think i’d be happy in college
column7: let alone as incredibly content and loved as i am right now.

column1: #metoo";"february 18th. it’s not my favorite day and february has been my least favorite month for the past few years. 3 years ago
column2: i was raped on a first date.

column1: to my rapist - a big fuck you and i hope your trial/conviction was a lesson for you. i hope you never do to anyone else
every year since then has been different - the first year i cried and stayed home all day
column2: last year i cried some and spent the day with ally and hunter eating burgers at one of my happy places
column3: and this year i actually forgot about what day it was until my family’s therapist texted me to ask if i wanted to talk or needed extra suppo today. when i realized what day it was
column4: i cried for a few minutes while my incredibly suppoive and kind boyfriend held me and reminded me that i was safe in that moment.

column1: i’ve actually been more stressed and anxious leading up to today than i have been during the day itself. today
column2: i spent the first half with my boyfriend - by far the most stellar human i’ve ever had the privilege of dating. we coincidentally got breakfast at the same café i sat at two years ago
column3: eating by myself and trying to prepare for the trial against my rapist that i would attend in a couple hours. then i got to spend a few hours with mariah
column5: which always makes my hea happy. we finally went to this cute little matcha café and ate to our hea’s content. and now
column6: i’m home in federal way eating teriyaki with my parents. it’s been a simple day
column7: with a lot of light heaed-ness and little joys. but it’s been a rough month
column8: with some added anxiety and extra hyper vigilance.

column1: my life is pretty busy right now
column2: i work at the ram 4 days
column3: at my internship at ryther 2 days
column4: and coaching 1 day. i have classes that i both enjoy and am ready to be done with. i am graduating in june from my dream school with a degree i am proud of. i have no idea what i’ll be doing after graduation
column5: but right now i am happy. i am suppoed and cared for. thank you to everyone who’s been a pa of my healing the past few years
column6: it really has been an arduous journey. i didn’t think i’d be happy in college
column7: let alone as incredibly content and loved as i am right now.

harvey weinstein domino ลามมากระชากหน้ากาวงการแฟชั่น ทำให้เหล่าผู้เกี่ยวข้องต้องเดือดร้อนไปตาม ๆ กันทั้ง karl templer

column1: ติดตามซีรีส์สรุปเหตุการณ์สำคัญแห่งปีโว้กได้ตลอดเดือนกุมภาพันธ์นี้!

;โว้กรวบรวมสุดยอดเรื่องเด่นในปีปฏิทินโว้กในช่วงเดือนกุมภาพันธ์ 2018 - กุมภาพันธ์ 2019 กับการล่วงละเมิดทางเพศ etoo harvey weinstein domino ลามมากระชากหน้ากาวงการแฟชั่น ทำให้เหล่าผู้เกี่ยวข้องต้องเดือดร้อนไปตาม ๆ กันทั้ง karl templer , patrick demarchelier ต้องออกมาปฏิเสธ โพสต์โซเชียลของ kate upton ที่กล่าวถึงการผูกมิตรของ guess กับ paul marciano ผู้ร่วมก่อตั้งที่เธออ้างว่าเคยจับหน้าอกจนเขาต้องลาออกทันควัน รวมถึง bruce weber และ mario testino ก็ถูกสำนักข่าวตีพิมพ์ข่าวด้านลบ ดีกรีเรื่องราวร้อนไปถึงซูเปอร์สตาร์ตัวแม่อย่าง beyoncé ที่ถึงขั้นซื้อหุ้นแบรนด์ ivy park ออกจากเครือ topshop ทันทีหลังจากมีข่าว philip green กับกระแสล่วงละเมิด แต่ scarlett johansson ใส่ชุดของแบรนด์ marchesa อดีตภรรยาของฮาร์วีย์บนพรมแดงของเม็ตกาล่าเพื่อสื่อว่า “ มลทินของสามีไม่เกี่ยวข้องกับภรรยาผู้ใสซื่อ ” ติดตามซีรีส์สรุปเหตุการณ์สำคัญแห่งปีโว้กได้ตลอดเดือนกุมภาพันธ์นี้ ! column3: let alone a good education for their children. in kentucky
column4: they had isolated mountain communities which could only get their books and reading material from one source… librarians on horseback.

column1: president franklin roosevelt was trying to figure out a way to resolve the great depression of the 1930s. his works progress administration created the pack horse library initiative to help americans become more literate so that they’d have a better chance of finding employment.
these librarians would adventure through muddy creeks and snowy hills just to deliver books to the people of these isolated areas.

the horseback librarians were mostly made up of women. they were paid salaries by the works progress administration. the rule was that libraries had to exist in the counties where books would be delivered. many of the local schools contributed to this effort by donating literature
these adventurous women on horseback would ride as much as 120 miles within a given week
column2: regardless of the terrain or weather conditions. sometimes
column3: they would have to finish their travels on foot if their destination was in a place too remote and tough for horses to go.

column2: the horseback book delivery program had ended because employment skyrocketed during world war ii.

column1: these women had to be locally known to people too or else those living in the mountains would not trust them.

column1: 18234;instagram;2018-11-01 18:29:28;FALSE;happy november !!! it feels good to get fresh air and twist the toxins out ❤️ i am 2 weeks postpartum and starting to feel like i’m getting the hang of mothering 3 babies 3 and under. not that it’s easy because it’s definitely not 😂but i feel like it’s right where i am supposed to be. being a mother is hard regardless of the number of kids you have but this is my path and it feels right for me. my family feels complete. “this too shall pass” “breathe” and “take one day at a time” have become my mantras (even more then they already were 😂) its important to make some time for yourself no matter how busy you are. even if it’s 5 minutes. making sure you are happy is a priority. i hope everyone is taking care of themselves today and every day 🙏❤️💫;;en;;;;;;0;;healing_with_yoga_;Joline;;0;False;6;0;0;61;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/5c8d4e48a8654dee374783b694f927f9/5D259FC5/t51.2885-15/e35/44710787_354016782090432_5747581891265921615_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;happy november !!! column1: 18255;instagram;2019-02-19 04:09:27;FALSE;"i debated about returning to the stage for this but you know what? i am doing this show in honor of my daddy ""daddy love"" as you all called him. he was/is my best friend and my ace! you all know how close we were and the special bond we had. he loved everything about my life and all the things that i am doing. i will continue to make my daddy and mommy proud! he would want me to keep pushing and living. this has been a tough year but i am a strong woman! come celebrate my daddy's life! i hope to see you all next thursday! monica mzdrummer and band

column1: 18270;instagram;2019-02-17 13:27:56;FALSE;"as a baby i was locked in the closet by my unstable mother. my father was murdered when i was a year and a half old.  at 3 my grandparents took me away from my mother .as a little girl i was sexually abused from 8-14 years old. at the same time my older sister committed suicide and my grandmother and me were the ones that found her. after this heartbreaking tragedy my grandparents checked out emotionally and i was left to pick up the pieces alone. they still rarely talk about my sisters death to this day.

healing from complex trauma is a lifelong journey with tons of ups and downs but i continue  to work on me every.single .day. i  do it for myself but i also do it for my children. they need all of me. and i need to be able to emotionally give them that . they deserve all the love. i am breaking the cycle of trauma. that is my purpose.

i was abandoned as a child. i was abused. i was traumatized . but that does not define me! i am strong. i am kind. and i know i can get through anything. through years of counseling and self love i am the person i needed when i was younger and i am the mother i needed when i was younger and i am just so grateful of that -that i could cry.

no matter what you have been through honor your truth - share you story. lift each-other up. most importantly love the child inside you! we all have our stuff that has made us who we are. let go of the guilt
column2: shame and pain and practice forgiveness. forgiving others who hurt you doesn’t mean you have to have them in your life. it’s doesn’t mean what they did was okay. you are just creating more space for your own healing. through forgiveness you are letting go of those heavy burdens they placed on you. they were never meant for you to carry but they made you the strong you that you are. give yourself the grace and unconditional love that you deserve 💗";;en;;;;;;0;;healing_with_yoga_;Joline;;0;False;12;0;0;44;https://instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net/vp/bdf35ee7b4fe613645e6a026a66efc8d/5D276438/t51.2885-15/e35/51126647_150498225952623_9126355504334783307_n.jpg?_nc_ht=instagram.fyvr3-1.fna.fbcdn.net;0;FALSE;FALSE;FALSE;english;"as a baby i was locked in the closet by my unstable mother. my father was murdered when i was a year and a half old.  at 3 my grandparents took me away from my mother .as a little girl i was sexually abused from 8-14 years old. at the same time my older sister committed suicide and my grandmother and me were the ones that found her. after this heartbreaking tragedy my grandparents checked out emotionally and i was left to pick up the pieces alone. they still rarely talk about my sisters death to this day.

column2: but i’ve spent the last several months working up to it. i’m learning to do things that terrify me
column3: because i never learned how to do them before. i was taught to always say yes
column4: and to make sure others were more comfortable than myself. these teachings left me cold and sobbing on my own floor after being assaulted by “a friend”. they left me taking a pregnancy test three weeks later. they led me down the dark road of depression
column5: where i suppressed so many emotions and trauma and i just didn’t feel anything for a year. i was numb. i only existed. i dimmed my personality and i put on weight to stop attracting attention to myself. it took me one year to realize i was depressed and two years to start to come out of it. i finally signed up and am currently halfway through a self defense class. i’m seeing everything i did wrong
column6: all the scenarios i could have used to escape
column7: and it’s so. damn. triggering. when my no’s weren’t enough
column8: i wish i had learned to escape. but i am learning now. it’s physically and emotionally exhausting
column9: but so empowering at the same time. don’t wait to take a class until you’re full of should haves. learn how to say no forcefully. learn how to defend yourself now. learn how to escape. i was naive and i was the perfect victim. don’t be me. if you or someone you know has been a victim
column10: don’t wait to get help. if you don’t know where to start
column11: dm me. i’ll help direct you. healing is possible. you’re not alone. .

column2: 이를 통해 기존의 물질적인 제도(문학 제도
column3: 문화 제도 등)에 저항하는 오큐파이 운동의 한 사례로 자리매김될 필요가 있다.

column2: 한국정신대문제대책협의회가 1992년부터 계속 진행하고 있는 수요 집회 역시 점령당한 신체를 애도하는 저항적 오큐파이 운동의 세계적인 사례이다.

column1: 2011년 ‘1000차’ 수요 집회를 기념하여 만들어진 평화비(소녀상)는 원래 기념물이었다.

;그리고 `` 최근 한국 사회에 나타난 성폭력 생존자들의 해시태그 운동도 온라인 담론 공간을 일시적으로 점거하면서 , 이를 통해 기존의 물질적인 제도 ( 문학 제도 , 문화 제도 등 ) 에 저항하는 오큐파이 운동의 한 사례로 자리매김될 필요가 있다 . 또한 , 한국정신대문제대책협의회가 1992년부터 계속 진행하고 있는 수요 집회 역시 점령당한 신체를 애도하는 저항적 오큐파이 운동의 세계적인 사례이다 . 2011년 ‘ 1000차 ’ 수요 집회를 기념하여 만들어진 평화비 ( 소녀상 ) 는 원래 기념물이었다 . 그러나 소녀상 ‘ 설치 ’ 를 영토 분쟁으로 매도하는 공격 때문에 역설적이지만 , 소녀상 설치 운동은 오큐파이 운동이 되고 있다 . '' ― 권명아 지음 , 『여자떼 공포 , 젠더 어펙트』 , 3부 2장 증강 현실적 신체를 기반으로 한 반기념 정치 구상 , 294쪽 책소개 2/25 저자강연회 자떼공포 큐파이 시태그운동 투 요집회 녀상 미니즘 ;[('그리고', 'NN'), ('``', '``'), ('최근', 'JJ'), ('한국', 'NN'), ('사회에', 'NNP'), ('나타난', column1: 18570;instagram;2019-02-19 01:32:13;FALSE;"i’ve spent 6 years (since i turned 20 & got ‘uni student jobs’ that were no longer illegally low wage) saving up for this gear/set up. 1 item a year + a couple of hand-me-downs (tnx @mei.swan.lim

@pantherpantherav 😉) . it’s been/is hard & slow to learn. especially when my life situation (#u don’t know my actual story) and a warped set of values placed on me by the society i’m surrounded by has demanded i put everything else first as my creative desires/ capacities are a ‘whim’ and “won’t make you money so don’t prioritise it” / “art won’t pay the bills” 😒👎🏽 + i was deprived of the memo during developmental years that “you are worthy & capable & you’re passions & creative personality are respectable & beautiful” (😒tnx a lot childhood & then college boys #metoo ) - now i have to keep telling myself “you’re not too old” and i set out to try and create music for the sake of music
column4: my sanity & contributing to the world of art as a means of positive social change. which is all i’ve ever truly yearned for. 🙌🏽💫 i’m dyslexic and make the dumbest mistakes each time i try and use all this tech. lol sometimes hours of hard work go pear shaped because of a dyslexia induced mistake🍐. but tnx to best husbo ever tech nerd & my perseverance. here’s to life lessons learnt
column5: better l8 than never 😏🙃🤙🏽 and to art💓 and to trying.

column1: 18587;instagram;2019-02-19 02:05:43;FALSE;"i first performed the vagina monologues at warren wilson college one decade ago. it was a super heavy experience for me. it was when i first started to talk about and accept my history with sexual assault. i think that being in a room full of woman talking about our vaginas
column2: was the first place i felt safe enough to begin those conversations. it’s truly a beautiful thing
column6: and to talk with an entire community of women.

column1: this friday will be my third year performing with the san marcos vagina monologues
column2: and i couldn’t be more honored to share my community of women with the world. these women are bad ass and beautiful and strong and smart and brave and creative and caring. and all the proceeds of the night will go to the hays caldwell women’s center
column3: so we can keep building a community that fights abuse and empowers our women to be the best versions of ourselves.

column1: 18597;instagram;2019-02-19 02:15:15;FALSE;"just a few hours till my birthday!! not just any birthday
column2: my 40th birthday!!! i love this poem by @rupikaur_ and it is the perfect thing to post for my birthday. ❤ #lettherehearsalsbegin ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
if you had told me that on my 40th birthday i would be unmarried and with no kids
column3: i would have imagined this birthday would be very depressing. haha! ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

column1: but i am so thankful i feel the complete opposite. my life has had lots of twists and turns in this 40 years of life. i have grown up to be a woman who loves herself. who has learned to fight for herself in the aftermath of being sexually assaulted. who tries to do a better job of fighting for the value of others each and every day. i have learned that growth isn't always fun
column2: but it is worth it. i have traveled around the world by myself several times. i take chances on myself and others all the time. i have learned that my worth is in no way lessened or increased by if i have a ring on my finger.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

column1: i am proud of the woman i have become so far
column2: and i am excited about the woman i will become with each passing day.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

column2: a 20-year-old woman in el salvador who was sentenced to 30 years in prison for giving birth to a stillborn baby in a toilet
column3: has been freed. el salvador’s supreme court overturned the sentence on friday
column4: ordering a new trial after hernández had served almost three years of her sentence. hernández gave birth in a toilet in 2016 and was rushed to hospital for losing large amounts of blood and losing consciousness. she was then charged with aggravated homicide after prosecutors argued that failing to seek antenatal care amounted to murder. hernández said she had been repeatedly raped by a gang member and didn’t realize she was pregnant. she said that she would have gone to a doctor if she had known if she was pregnant. however
column5: the judge at the time did not believe that hernández did not know she was pregnant and believed she didn’t seek medical care because she didn’t want the baby and threw the baby into the toilet to kill him. medical experts could not determine whether the foetus had died in her womb or just after being born. abortion is illegal in all circumstances in el salvador
column6: and dozens of women have been imprisoned for having miscarriages or stillbirths. (📷: getty)

column2: i’ve gotten to know a bit of this survivor’s tremendous heart. she is so magnanimous with her kindness- it’s  truly an honor to include her story. shelly is a survivor of childhood sexual abuse at the hands of a female family friend. as a voice in the survivor advocate community
column3: i’ll attest that we don’t spend as much time on the subject of non-male sexual abusers (not to minimize the link between toxic masculinity and rape culture. it’s real and huge
column4: -but that’s not what i’m talking about today). because there is less of it
column5: this kind of abuse receives less attention. so these survivors often feel invisible and don’t get the care and resources they need to heal from these very real traumas. such was the case when it happened to shelly. she describes being made to feel so powerless by this woman- for *years*. when she did tell her family
column6: they didn’t seem to care. they continue to maintain multiple connections with her abuser. •

column1: sexual abuse itself does not have a gender. it’s true that most perpetrators are men (and that a massive problem lies within the patriarchy)
column2: but it does not mean that survivors of female and non-male sexual abuse are lesser. i’m so glad that shelly knew this in her own heart when her parents made her feel otherwise. and while it breaks mine that she did not get the familial support she needed
column3: i’m grateful for the resilience of her soul. she has the fortitude to wake up every day and tell *herself* that she “is not dirty or disgusting
column4: that she deserves love and her truth matters.” she has the presence of mind to reach out to other survivors
column5: and she has a graceful self-awareness that is astounding (more on that later). she is an example that
column6: while the survivor peer advocacy community *is* absolutely essential to our healing

column3: marks seven years since i left my abuser. on this day in 2012

column13: and there has been release.  there has been previously unfathomable levels of self-love

column3: is so so worth it. you are so so so so so very worth it.

column1: there is hope; there is infinite healing for what feels like your infinite pain.
regardless of the validity of total cell regeneration over the course of seven years
column2: my regained strength alone has made me new.

column4: and i am happier and healthier than ever.

column2: know there is hope. there are place and people out there who will help you love and heal again and who await you with open and totally compassionate arms.

column1: i am: not shivering in this cold sea
the photos i’m sharing this week are of me
column2: from my series of portraits in nature. as a 66-year-old woman and emerging artist

column1: * the natural desire to be unclothed outdoors

column1: * a newly discovered quality of self-acceptance for my aging self;

column1: 18697;instagram;2019-02-19 05:12:18;FALSE;"it took a year-and-a-half but i was finally able to walk away from my old church. during that time the question was consistently posed to me: why are you involved
column2: are you taking care of you
column3: are you finished now? now? now?

column1: it was a year-and-a-half of getting stronger
column2: more clear and confident in what i had experienced. as that happened
column3: the attachment to those who needed me to carry the emotional discomfort naturally dissolved. for many victims of abuse in the church
column4: isolation is one result of coming forward. the community peels away like layers on an onion: those who believe you are lying
column5: those who cannot stand to see intense sadness and trauma
column6: those who support you as long as that doesn't mean going public.

column1: i am so grateful. one of the biggest fears people have is the fear of being alone or rejected. that no longer plagues me which can feel bizarre!

column2: i have been wondering what victims should do. what strikes me the most is that these disciples are told to walk away. not ""stay and argue
column4: not ""make your life's cause to convert this particular house."" leave.

column1: 18707;instagram;2019-02-19 05:18:59;FALSE;"- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture
column2: so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs
column4: basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

column1: is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying
column2: christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse
column3: because if you do not respect the agency of people
column4: anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally
column5: information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

column1: millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen

column1: it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

column1: 犯罪者の兄のいるせいで
どこへ行っても身辺調査をされ
この放送のあった時期が
私がセクハラ、パワハラ、いじめ、
通勤経路でつきまとわれている真っ只中
私が東野圭吾さんが好きなのをわかっていて、この映画を見るのをわかっていて
映画のようにどこまでも、どこへ行っても追い詰めるよ。という意味に受け取れます。
ワンシーンに映るプリンターも過去に私が使っていたもの。
大型ゴミに出していたが
朝8時から収集ですと聞いていたのに
朝7時代に出勤のため家を出るときにはもうなかった。
そしてその収集依頼の電話をしたのが社内だった。
偶然が重なりすぎると怖い
というか私に見せるため
どこまでも付きまとうよ
と言うメッセージに受け取れます。

column1: 18994;instagram;2019-02-19 12:32:23;FALSE;"two surya kiran aircraft collided into each other and crashed moments after that at about 11.50am while practicing for the 12th edition of aero india here on tuesday. one pilot has been confirmed dead
column2: while two others have sustained injuries.

column1: the surya kiran aerobatic team has been an eye-catcher at multiple aero india shows and has recently upgraded to flying the hawk aircraft. they earlier flew the kiran trainer aircraft
column2: which has been decommissioned by the indian air force (iaf). “today morning at around 11.50am
column3: two hawk aircraft of surya kiran aerobatic team of iaf crashed while practicing for the aero india air show. three pilots were occupants. two pilots ejected and have been evacuated to the command hospital. third pilot sustained fatal injuries. damage to life and property in the vicinity of crash site is being ascertained
column4: ” iaf spokesperson said in a statement

column1: while the iaf has ordered a court of inquiry (coi)
column2: which will investigate the cause of the accident
column3: eye-witnesses accounts and videos show that one of the planes’ nose collided into the other
column4: making it very difficult to recover for the pilots.

column1: the rest of the surya kiran team (seven aircraft) landed in hal airport and has been based there for now. while all surya kiran aircraft (hawk) are twin seaters
column2: the team generally flies with one pilot. on tuesday
column3: one of the aircraft had two pilots in them
column4: both of whom ejected to safe. “one of the pilots has fractures on both his legs and has been shifted to the operating theatre
column5: while some scans are being performed on the other
column6: ” a source said. the third pilot’s body is yet to be brought to command hospital. once it reaches there
column7: a post mortem would be performed and the body will be handed over to the family

column1: please note this post has sensitive pictures and videos that could trouble a person
